    <title type="html"><![CDATA[Setting FTP server with vsftpd]]></title>
    <link href="lxp121.github.io/15139073479032.html"/>
    <updated>2017-12-22T09:49:07+08:00</updated>
    <id>lxp121.github.io/15139073479032.html</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[
<ul>
<li>Install vsftpd</li>
</ul>

<pre><code class="language-bash">sudo apt-get install vsftpd
</code></pre>

<ul>
<li>Configure vsftpd</li>
</ul>

<pre><code class="language-bash">sudo vim /etc/vsftpd.conf
</code></pre>

<p>Modify following lines to restrict user.</p>

<pre><code class="language-bash">anonymous_enable=NO
local_enable=YES
write_enable=YES
chroot_local_user=YES
loca_root=/home/ftp
</code></pre>

<ul>
<li>Add ftp user (or you can use local id)</li>
</ul>

<pre><code class="language-bash">sudo useradd -d /home/ftp -M ftpuser
sudo passwd ftpuser
</code></pre>

<ul>
<li>Change permission</li>
</ul>

<pre><code class="language-bash">sudo chmod a-w /home/ftp
</code></pre>

<ul>
<li>Configure pam.d/vsftpd to allow local user id</li>
</ul>

<pre><code class="language-bash">sudo vim /etc/pam.d/vsftp
# auth   required pam_shells.so
</code></pre>

<ul>
<li>Restart the vsftpd</li>
</ul>

<pre><code class="language-bash">sudo /etc/init.d/vsftpd restart
</code></pre>

]]></content>
